 is the wife who provides the climate, the husband the landscape.', 38041, 0), (475928, 'Sensual pleasures have the fleeting brilliance of a comet a happy marriage has the tranquillity of a lovely sunset. ', 3199, 0), (475929, 'A journey is like marriage. The certain way to be wrong is to think you control it.', 1070, 0), (475930, 'The most happy marriage I can picture or imagine to myself would be the union of a deaf man to a blind woman.', 1910, 0), (475931, 'My decision to end my marriage was such a risk to lose ratings and lose my fan base. I had to take that risk for my inner peace and to be happy with myself.', 34530, 0), (475932, 'When you make the sacrifice in marriage, you''re sacrificing not to each other but to unity in a relationship.', 1123, 0), (475933, 'I was against gay marriage until I realized I didn''t have to get one.', 70628, 0), (475934, 'A good marriage is one which allows for change and growth in the individuals and in the way they express their love.', 442, 0), (475935, 'Friendship is the marriage of the soul, and this marriage is liable to divorce.', 808, 0), (475936, 'I think that gay marriage should be between a man and a woman.', 12194, 0), (475937, 'As to marriage or celibacy, let a man take which course he will, he will be sure to repent.', 1595, 0), (475938, 'The biggest financial pitfall in life is divorce. And the biggest reason for divorce is marriage.', 11192, 0), (475939, 'Where there''s marriage without love, there will be love without marriage.', 1077, 0), (475940, 'Married men live longer than single men. But married men are a lot more willing to die.', 13016, 0), (475941, 'The secret of a good marriage is forgiving your partner for marrying you in the first place.', 4733, 0), (475942, 'I have close family members as well as lots of close friends who are gay. Many of them strongly support gay marriage.', 56229, 0), (475943, 'I believe the home and marriage is the foundation of our society and must be protected.', 4008, 0), (47